<PageLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="What cookies Admin's Choice uses, why, and how you can control them."
  updated="June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how Admin's Choice uses them,
    and how you can control them. It should be read alongside our
    <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What cookies are</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website.
    They are widely used to make sites work, to remember preferences, and to
    provide information to site owners and advertisers.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use cookies</h2>
  <p>The cookies on this site fall into a few categories:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Essential cookies.</strong> Needed for the site to function and to
      remember basic preferences such as light or dark mode. These cannot
      meaningfully be switched off.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Analytics cookies.</strong> Help us understand how visitors use the
      site so we can improve it. These collect information in aggregate.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Advertising cookies.</strong> When advertising is active on the
      site, third-party vendors including Google may set cookies to serve and
      measure ads. Google's advertising cookies (including the DoubleClick
      cookie) may be used to show ads based on your visits to this and other
      sites.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Some cookies are set by third parties, such as advertising and analytics
    providers. These are governed by those third parties' own policies. You can
    learn more and opt out of personalised advertising at
    <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>
    and
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Controlling cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Most browsers let you view, manage, and delete cookies through their
    settings, and to block cookies from some or all sites. Blocking essential
    cookies may affect how parts of the site work. For guidance, see your
    browser's help pages.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Cookie Policy as our use of cookies changes. The "Last
    updated" date above reflects the most recent revision.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
